<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='496173' id='t-496173'>and there is not a single note played</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='498671' id='t-498671'>for four minutes and 33 seconds.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='502540' id='t-502540'>And, at once enraging and enrapturing,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='507254' id='t-507254'>Cage shows us that even
when there are no strings</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='510166' id='t-510166'>being plucked by fingers
or hands hammering piano keys,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='515238' id='t-515238'>still there is music,
